text: By-Wy Creek is a stream in the U.S. state of Mississippi. It is a tributary to Biba Wila Creek. By-Wy Creek is a name derived from the Choctaw language meaning "leaning white oak". ==References== Category:Rivers of Mississippi Category:Bodies of water of Oktibbeha County, Mississippi
title: By-Wy Creek (Biba Wila Creek tributary)
